messages.text: I’m here, Ada. Where r u?
I woke up in the back of Declan’s truck.
We’re parked out in the woods but he’s gone.
I don’t know if he’s coming back
You were supposed to head straight to Dallas.
Do u still have my guns?
Do you have my god damned guns with you or not?!
Are the keys in the truck?
If so, start it up and get out of there.
Shouldn’t I wait and see if he comes back?
you’re not safe until you’re far away from Fort Hood and with me.
My leg still kinda hurts from the wreck last night.
Where are you?! I need you! ☹
Ada, as much as this breaks my heart to do...
I’m gonna level with you, because I love you.
You need to grow up, and I mean right now.
Don’t text. Don’t whine. Just read.
The world is going to fall apart today.
So you don’t get to be a kid any more.
And if you don’t start doing what I tell you, when I tell you to do it…
Now. ARE the keys in the truck?
Do you know where you are?
No, but I hear rumbling in the distance.
Close enough to shake the ground.
the Air Force is saturation bombing..
Destroying the base and the surrounding area.
The U.S. Air Force is bombing Ft. Hood?!
There is no more Ft. Hood.
Our personnel did the best they could to control the outbreak at the base…
but once they were overrun, the President had to expand the containment area.
No. And you were supposed to be 200 miles from there by now.
Jesus, dad, the bombs are getting closer.
I can hear the planes now too.
Then you need to find Sgt. Delaney and GET OUT OF THERE!
Search the area. Shout his name.
He may be injured and unable to get to you.
No answer. But I’ll keep looking.
Good girl. And I want you armed at all times.
Keep shouting. And if you see anyone who’s not Sgt. Delaney, shoot them.
I walked out into a clearing and.. She’s just standing there.
Jesus, dad.. it’s horrible.. she looks so..
She’s not. She’s… staring at me.
That’s all she can do in the daylight.
And she’s not your mother any more.
What matters is that you get out of there.
Ada, if it were anyone but your mother I would make you shoot her.
There’s no bringing anyone back from this.
I can’t do that to her.
I know. I’m not asking you to.
But I need you to remember what I said if you want to stay alive.
Hang on.. I hear Sgt Delaney calling my name.
R u saying I can’t trust him now?
But we need him to get you out of there.
I’ll be careful. Hang on while I find out what’s up.
Holy shit! That was close! I could feel the heat from that one!
We’re back at the truck.. but the bombs are so close now.
Sgt Delaney is filling the truck now.
Gas – we ran out. He’s filling up more.
In the middle of the woods?
Said he owns a cabin nearby.
Had some extra cans in storage.
He’s not taking you to meet me in Dallas.
Dallas is north of Ft. Hood.
Does he know that you know he’s lying?
Then go along with it for now.
Do whatever’s necessary to get out of there...
But don’t turn your back on Declan for a second.
Tell him to get on a main road and get to I-35.
I will. And I’ll text you when I get to the highway.
And Ada… whatever he’s up to, Declan can’t know you’re on to him.
He won’t read my texts. Trust me.
